{"id":32427,"date":"2019-06-22T15:22:56","date_gmt":"2019-06-22T11:22:56","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=32427"},"modified":"2024-08-23T11:44:05","modified_gmt":"2024-08-23T07:44:05","slug":"prophet-leaves-book-sunnah","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/22\/prophet-leaves-book-sunnah\/","title":{"rendered":"Farewell Sermon: Final advice to follow Quran and Sunnah"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Ibn Abbas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, addressed the people during the farewell sermon, saying, \u201c<strong>Satan has despaired that he will ever be worshiped in your lands. Rather, he is pleased for you to obey him in other matters, among your deeds you consider insignificant. Beware, O people! I have surely left among you what you must firmly hold to, by which you will never be led astray again: the Book of Allah and the Sunnah of His Prophet. Verily, the Muslim is a brother of another Muslim, the Muslims are brethren. It is not lawful for a man to take his brother&#8217;s wealth unless he gives it freely and willingly. You may not wrong each other. Do not turn back to the ways of unbelievers after me, striking the necks of each other.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Mustadrak \u2018ala\u0301 al-S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323ayn 318<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0633\u064d \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u062e\u064e\u0637\u064e\u0628\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0633\u064e